<h1 style="color:rgb(69, 17, 17)">ABOUT SAVITHRI</h1>
<img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/bf/ff/b8/bfffb81d7ad1aef43240ae0ef2788ce9.jpg" width="1",height="2>
<img src="savithri.jpg" alt="Savithri Actress">

<p>
Savithri was one of the greatest actresses in Telugu and Tamil cinema.
She was popularly known as "Mahanati" because of her powerful acting
and emotional performances. She acted in more than 250 films and became
one of the most respected actresses in Indian cinema history.
</p>

<h1>Early Life</h1>

<ol>
<li style="color:blue">Born: December 6, 1936</li>
<li style="color:blue">Place: Chirravuru, Andhra Pradesh</li>
<li style="color:blue">Parents: Nissankara Guravayya and Subhadramma</li>
<li style="color:blue">She learned classical dance at a young age.</li>
</ol>

<h1>Film Career</h1>

<p style="color:rgb(7, 6, 5)">
Savithri entered the film industry at a young age.
Her natural acting style made her very popular among audiences.
She worked with many legendary actors in South Indian cinema
and later also directed and produced films.
</p>

<h1>Famous Movies</h1>

<ul>
<li>Maya Bazaar</li>
<li>Missamma</li>
<li>Devadasu</li>
<li>Gundamma Katha</li>
<li>Chivaraku Migiledi</li>
</ul>

<h1>Awards and Achievements</h1>

<p>
Savithri received many awards and recognition for her acting.
She was called "Mahanati" because of her extraordinary talent.
Her performances are still admired by many actors today.
</p>

<h1>Legacy</h1>

<p>
Savithri is remembered as one of the greatest actresses
in South Indian cinema. Her life story inspired the movie
"Mahanati". Her acting continues to inspire many people
in the film industry.
</p>

